FBIS3-15034 "drsov041_v_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 Lithuania President Remains Most Popular Politician WS0103161294 Tallinn BNS in English 1330 GMT 1 Mar 94 WS0103161294 Tallinn BNS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vilnius, Mar 01, BNS -- The most recent public opinion poll in Lithuania indicates that President Algirdas Brazauskas continues to top the list of most popular politicians after a year spent in office. The principal tendency remains the same -- political leaders are gradually losing popularity. Aloyzas Sakalas, leader of the Social Democratic Party, was the only exception during the period between mid-January and mid-February. The results of the poll conducted by the British-Lithuanian Baltic Surveys company suggest the following list of top ten Lithuanian politicians: Algirdas Brazauskas -- 56 percent /-2/ Egidijus Bickauskas -- 50 percent /-3/ Romualdas Ozolas -- 46 percent /-1/ Kazimieras Antanavicius -- 41 percent /0/ Vytautas Landsbergis -- 35 percent /-5/ Adolfas Slezevicius -- 33 percent /-4/ Gediminas Vagnorius -- 28 percent /0/ Aloyzas Sakalas -- 28 percent /+1/ Ceslovas Jursenas -- 27 percent /-1/ Povilas Gylys -- 18 percent /0/
